    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look poised for a high-ceiling outing today, led by **Jackson Merrill** (72.59) and **Kyle Tucker** (71.89). Both outfielders draw favorable matchups against right-handed arms in Burke and McGreevy, respectively. **Jackson Merrill** is a particularly high-leverage start; his score is buoyed by an 87% stolen base threat against a slow-delivering pitcher, maximizing our scarcest category. Meanwhile, **Drake Baldwin** (68.14) benefits from a prime lineup slot at #2 and a park factor boost, making him our most efficient catcher play today. Despite facing a left-hander, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** remains a lock at 60.85, as his elite ability to sustain production against southpaws through pure contact quality keeps his floor high even when the platoon splits aren't strictly in his favor.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's card was bypassing **Coby Mayo** (53.08) for a spot in the utility or infield slots. While **Coby Mayo** presents a legitimate threat against Weathers, he ultimately fell behind the reliability of **Jacob Wilson** (62.15) and **Josh Jung** (60.72), both of whom are projected for higher daily output in more favorable park conditions. The primary risk to monitor is **Gunnar Henderson**, whose score of 56.12 is depressed by a significant 15% penalty due to the platoon disadvantage against the lefty Weathers. However, we are keeping him in the lineup to capitalize on his elite stolen base potential, as the matchup against a slow-moving delivery creates a unique \"green light\" scenario that outweighs the raw projection drop.",
